</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64392670">
<p>When I started reading the description, I felt sure that they were going to say that pulsed charging burned up the tips of the dendrites that form inside the batteries, thus inhibiting their growth, but we've known that for <a href="https://pubs.acs.org/doi/10.1021/jz500207a" title="acs.org">a decade</a> [acs.org].  So my initial reaction was "Yeah, no kidding, of course it will."  But unless I'm misunderstanding, this is yet a second, unrelated reason to do so.</p><p>The only real question is why we haven't been doing it for a decade.  Unless some a**hole took out a patent on it or something.<nobr> <wbr></nobr>:-)</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64392670">
